p: In 2006–2010, amongst HIV diagnoses attributed to male-to-male sex, the highest proportion were among Australian-born men, followed by men born in South-East Asia, North-West Europe, Oceania, the Americas, North-East Asia, Southern and Eastern Europe, Sub-Saharan Africa, North Africa and the Middle East and Southern and Central Asia. In 2011–2015, the highest proportion were among Australian-born men, followed by men born in South-East Asia, North-West Europe, North-East Asia, Oceania, the Americas, Southern and Eastern Europe, Southern and Central Asia, Sub-Saharan Africa, and North Africa and the Middle East.
